# Key Manager - Cline Project Rules

## Project Overview
Key Manager is a secure cryptocurrency key storage application with CLI and GUI interfaces.
It encrypts wallet data (24-word mnemonics, addresses, account info) using AES-256-GCM with Argon2id key derivation.
Designed for portable USB deployment alongside a local CLI workflow.

**Current production version: v4.0** (June 2026) - Price Feeds + Wallet Balances + Go Online Toggle. GUI is branded "ColdStack"; CLI source remains "key_manager" (script-mode only, CLI EXE deprecated). v3 adds BIP39 derivation. v4 adds balance fetching + CoinGecko price feeds.

## Versioning

Key Manager uses semantic versioning for releases. v1 is the original display-only GUI; v3 adds BIP39 mnemonic derivation.

| Version | Description | Key Files |
|---------|-------------|-----------|
| v1 | Original GUI - display-only | `src/gui_main.py`, `build_gui.py` |
| v2 | GUI Add functionality - create accounts, add addresses, add mnemonics | `src/gui_main_v2.py`, `build_gui_v2.py` |
| v3 | GUI BIP39 derivation - derive addresses/keys from mnemonics | `src/gui_main_v3.py`, `build_gui_v3.py`, `src/derivation_engine.py` |
| v3.1 | ColdStack rebrand + Check for Updates button | `src/gui_main_v3_1.py`, `build_gui_v3_1.py`, `key_manager_gui_v3_1.spec` |
| v4.0 | Price Feeds + Wallet Balances + Go Online | `src/gui_main_v4.py`, `build_gui_v4.py`, `src/balance_engine.py`, `src/price_engine.py` |

### Versioning Rules (MUST follow for all future versions)
1. New versions introduce a `_v<N>` suffix on all new/modified working files (e.g., `gui_main_v2.py`, `build_gui_v2.py`).
2. Previous-version files are preserved untouched as the baseline - never edit `gui_main.py` or `build_gui.py` (these are v1).
3. Core files of the previous version are backed up in the `backups/` directory with a `_v1` suffix (e.g., `backups/gui_main_v1.py`, `backups/build_gui_v1.py`, `backups/README_v1.md`, `backups/STATUS_v1.md`). This enables restoration.
4. Shared infrastructure (`crypto_engine.py`, `backup_engine.py`, `main.py`) is extended backward-compatibly - both v1 and v2 use the same crypto/KeyManager core.
5. EXE outputs in `USB_DEPLOYMENT/` are overwritten with the latest version build. The previous EXE is backed up to `backups/` before overwrite.
6. Documentation (`.clinerules`, `README.md`, `STATUS.md`) is updated with each version release.

